This release freezes the first public structural claim version of RJN Voynich Grammar.

Core claim:
Voynichese is a recursive hierarchical process-operator grammar. Voynich tokens are not ordinary words, but compressed operator-chains parsed sequence-by-sequence.

This release documents:
- witness-control protocol
- transcription baseline
- conservative correction rule
- primitive operator inventory
- macro-sequence grammar
- parser model
- diagrammatic grammar
- cross-regime claim hierarchy

Author: Ronny Juul Nielsen
Public release: June 2026
